'''Aboukar Hassan Adani''' (born 30 June 1968) is a [[long-distance runner]] who competed internationally for [[Somalia]].

Adani competed at the [[1988 Summer Olympics]] in [[Seoul]] and the [[1996 Summer Olympics]] in [[Atlanta]], in 1988 he competed in the [[Athletics at the 1988 Summer Olympics – Men's 5000 metres|5000 metres]] and finished 13th in his heat so did not advance in the next round, eight years later in the [[Athletics at the 1996 Summer Olympics – Men's 5000 metres|5000 metres]] he again finished 13th so not advancing again.<ref>[https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ad/aboukar-hassan-adani-1.html Sports Reference Profile]</ref>

