==Football career== On 4 August 2013, Califo made his professional debut with [[U.D. Oliveirense|Oliveirense]] in a [[2013–14 Taça da Liga]] match against [[S.C. Covilhã|Sporting Covilhã]], when he started and played the full game.<ref>{{cite news | date=4 August 2013| title=Covilhã-Oliveirense 1-1| url=http://www.lpfp.pt/taca_liga/pages/jogo.aspx?epoca=20132014&jornada=3&jogo=8823| publisher=''LPFP''| accessdate=}}</ref> In the first match of the [[2013–14 Segunda Liga]] season against [[F.C. Penafiel|Penafiel]] on the 11 August, he made his league debut.<ref>{{cite news | date=11 August 2013 | title=Penafiel-Oliveirense 1-0| url=http://www.lpfp.pt/segunda_liga/pages/jogo.aspx?epoca=20132014&jornada=1&jogo=8352| publisher=''LPFP''| accessdate=}}</ref>
Internationally, Califo made his senior début for [[Guinea Bissau national football team|Guinea Bissau]] on 19 July 2014.<ref>[http://africansoccer.weebly.com/botswana-vs-guinea-bissau-can---19714.html Botswana vs. Guinea Bissau (CAN - 19.7.14)] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20140720180857/http://africansoccer.weebly.com/botswana-vs-guinea-bissau-can---19714.html |date=2014-07-20 }}</ref>
