{{Infobox Organization | name = Federação Catarinense de Futebol | image = | size = | map = | formation = April 12, 1924<ref name="Book">{{cite book|title=Escudos dos Times do Mundo Inteiro|publisher=Panda Books|author=Rodolfo Rodrigues|year=2009|page=36}}</ref> | type = [[List of international sport federations]] | membership = | headquarters = [[Balneário Camboriú]], [[Santa Catarina (state)|Santa Catarina]], [[Brazil]] | leader_title = [[President]] | leader_name = [[Francisco Novelletto Neto]] | language = [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] | website = [http://www.fcf.com.br/ fcf.com.br] }} The '''Federação Catarinense de Futebol''' ([[English language|English]]: Football Association of Santa Catarina state) was founded on April 12, 1924, and manages all the official [[association football|football]] tournaments within the state of [[Santa Catarina (state)|Santa Catarina]], which are the [[Campeonato Catarinense]], the [[Campeonato Catarinense (lower levels)|Campeonato Catarinense lower levels]] and the [[Copa Santa Catarina]], and represents the clubs at the [[Brazilian Football Confederation|Brazilian Football Confederation (CBF)]].
