'''Marcerra United Football Club''' is a semi-professional football club based in [[Kuala Lumpur]]. The club last competed in the [[Malaysia FAM League]], the third tier of the Malaysian football league, in 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://inikanbola.my/2018/01/15/sejauh-mana-pasukan-baru-akan-bertahan/|title=Sejauh manakah pasukan baru akan bertahan|publisher=Inikanbola.my|accessdate=7 March 2018}}</ref>

The team also competes in the [[Kuala Lumpur League]], a state league.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.sinarharian.com.my/sukan/marcerra-united-alami-kekalahan-pertama-1.780354|title=Marcerra United alami kekalahan pertama|publisher=SinarHarian.com.my|accessdate=8 March 2018}}</ref>

In 2018, the management of Marcerra United also has taken over the management of [[Malaysia Premier League]] club [[Kuantan FA]], and renamimg the club to Marcerra Kuantan FA.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sports247.my/v1/2018/02/marcerra-kuantan-fa-akhirnya-buka-mulut|title=Marcerra Kuantan FA akhirnya buka mulut|publisher=Sports247.my|accessdate= 8 March 2018}}</ref>

As a result of financial problems, Marcerra United pulled out of the [[2018 Malaysia FAM Cup]] league on 20 July 2018, with the team's result expunged from the league. This means they shared the same fate of their other club, Marcerra Kuantan, who pulled out of [[2018 Malaysia Premier League]] with the same financial issue.<ref>https://www.fam.org.my/piala-fam-2018</ref>

