{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Petworth Park New Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Petworth]], [[Sussex]] | establishment = 1844 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year2 = 1849 | club2 = [[Sussex County Cricket Club|Sussex]] | year1 = 1844-1845 | club1 = [[Petworth Cricket Club]] | date = 27 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/690.html Ground profile }}
'''Petworth Park New Ground''' is a [[cricket]] ground in the shadow of [[Petworth House]], [[Petworth]], [[Sussex]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1844, when [[Petworth Cricket Club]] played the [[Marylebone Cricket Club]] in the first [[first-class cricket|first-class]] match held at the ground. From 1844-1845, the ground held two further first-class matches when Petworth Cricket Club played [[Hampshire county cricket teams|Hampshire]] and the Marylebone Cricket Club. [[Sussex County Cricket Club|Sussex]] played a single first-class match at the ground against [[Surrey County Cricket Club|Surrey]] in 1849.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/690_f.html First-Class Matches played on Petworth Park New Ground]</ref>
Despite the final recorded match on the ground being in 1961 when Petworth played South Hampstead,<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/690_misc.html Other matches played on Petworth Park New Ground]</ref> the ground continues to be used to this day and in local domestic cricket is the home venue of Petworth Park Cricket Club.<ref>[http://petworth.play-cricket.com/home/home.asp Petworth Park Cricket Club] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20120713101913/http://petworth.play-cricket.com/home/home.asp |date=2012-07-13 }}</ref>
