{{Orphan|date=February 2009}}
The '''Vientiane Buffalos''' rugby football club (sometimes spelled ''Buffaloes'') was founded in 1998 by [[rugby union]] playing expatriates in the capital of [[Laos]]. The club has grown gradually since then and is a full member of the [[Lao Rugby Federation]] (LRF). As well as men's contact rugby ([[Rugby sevens|sevens]], tens and fifteen-a-side), the club organises touch rugby tournaments involving women and children. Members of the Buffalos have been instrumental in promoting the sport in Laos, setting up the LRF and establishing a Lao national team and other clubs to play against.

