{{Infobox swimmer | name= Zakia Nassar | image= | imagesize= | caption = | fullname = Zakiya Nassar | nicknames = | nationality = {{PLE}} | strokes = Freestyle | club = | collegeteam = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1987|4|2}} | birth_place = [[Bethlehem]], Palestine | death_date = | death_place = | height = {{height|m=1.62|precision=0}} | weight = | medaltemplates= }}
'''Zakiya Nassar''', sometimes spelled "Zakia" ({{lang-ar|زكية نصار}}), born April 2, 1987 in Bethlehem, Palestine),<ref name=GM>[https://www.theglobeandmail.com/servlet/story/RTGAM.20080707.wswimmers07/BNStory/International/home?cid=al_gam_mostview "For Palestinian swimmers, it's a chance to swim"], ''Globe and Mail'', July 7, 2008</ref> is an Olympic swimmer from [[State of Palestine|Palestine]].<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20080916182539/http://results.beijing2008.cn/WRM/ENG/BIO/Athlete/6/236366.shtml Nassar's bio] from the 2008 Olympics website; retrieved 2009-07-09.</ref>
She [[Palestine at the 2008 Summer Olympics|represented Palestine]] at the [[2008 Summer Olympics]] in [[Beijing]]. In the lead-up to the Games, her coach, relayed by the media, commented that Nassar faced severe difficulties in training, due to her lack of access to a swimming pool. ''[[The Globe and Mail]]'' reported that "[t]here is no Olympic-sized pool in the Palestinian territories and no budget to speak of for the Palestinian Olympic swimmers".<ref name=GM/> Nassar told the media that she was receiving no support from the Palestinian authorities, that she was able to swim once a month "at best", and that she feared a disastrous performance in Beijing.<ref>[http://www.courriersport.com/actu/jo/160408_Palestine.asp "JEUX OLYMPIQUES: Les Palestiniens à rude épreuve"], ''Courier international''</ref><ref>[http://www.ynetnews.com/articles/0,7340,L-3527840,00.html "From Jenin to Beijing"], [[Ynetnews]], April 5, 2008</ref> The [[Israel]]i authorities subsequently granted her authorisation to swim in a pool in [[Jerusalem]].<ref>[http://www.ynetnews.com/articles/0,7340,L-3529275,00.html "Palestinian Olympic runner receives exit permit"], Ynetnews, April 8, 2008</ref>
Nassar won her heat in the [[Swimming at the 2008 Summer Olympics – Women's 50 metre freestyle|50 metre freestyle event]], but her time of 31.97 was not sufficient for her to advance to the next round.<ref>[http://africa.reuters.com/sport/news/usnBAN549894.html "Beijing's youngest is leader of the laggards"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080908040055/http://africa.reuters.com/sport/news/usnBAN549894.html |date=2008-09-08 }}, Reuters, August 15, 2008</ref>
Nassar lives in [[Bethlehem]] and, as of 2008, is studying dentistry at the [[Arab American University]] in [[Jenin]].<ref name=GM/>
